Text.Value: Ha! Not so spineless now, am I?
Swing, parry, strike - nngh. Damn, damn, damn!

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Practicing his swing. Not looking at player.

Text.Value: Step, parry, strike - damn it! It's just not... agh!

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Trying and failing at swordplay practice
EditorData.NodeContext: Frustrated. Practicing swordplay with little success - then reacts with alarm upon seeing a gith

Text.Value: Like this, you mean? Step-step, strike! Yes!
You're spineless. You should practice grovelling on your knees, not swordplay.
Try hitting the target.
A question? I suppose it's worth a try...
Show him how to coil his shoulder muscles into a more intimidating stance before striking.
Resume your flailing then, before I give you real cause to yelp.
Like this? All right... step-step, strike - UGH!
Good advice - If I had two copper, I'd owe you one.

EditorData.NodeContext: Grateful (but he has nothing to give the player)

Text.Value: Sorry, sorry. I've just never seen... your face is... well. I should get back to it.

EditorData.NodeContext: Apologising, A little unnerved by a gith

Text.Value: Spineless? Well I'll show you!
Step, parry, strike - ugh. Again, again.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Practicing his swing. Not looking at player.

Text.Value: I could show you a thing or two, if you're a willing pupil.
RrrrrarghWAGGH! Brace and step, swivel, swing! Yes!
Out of my head!
You're right. I need to clear my head.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: He gives a long sigh, then nods.

Text.Value: Don't let the druids hear you say that - they're itching for an excuse to get rid of us.
I'll suffer embarrassment so long as I survive. I just hope the druids don't make that harder than it is already.
Hopefully it's just the goblins we have to worry about - the druids are treating us like vermin.

EditorData.NodeContext: He's still got misgivings - the goblins aren't the only threat

Text.Value: He was only a boy. And I just... just froze while the worg tore his head clean off. Never again.

EditorData.NodeContext: A memory. He recalls a time he froze in combat. But he still feels guilty and unsure.

Text.Value: Swing, parry, strike - nngh. Damn, damn, damn!

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Practicing his swing. Not looking at player.

Text.Value: Put one foot in front of the other. Let momentum aid your strikes.
You need discipline, focus. Fix your gaze to a point, then guide your strikes to it.
Inspire fear with a war cry - loosen bowels before you spill them - hrath ajak!
You have a better way? 'Cause I'm all ears.
One last thing - don't shout out your moves like that. Spoils the surprise for your foe.
I think you made it worse. Keep the advice to yourself next time.
Step, parry, strike - damn it! It's just not landing.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Practicing his swing. Not looking at player.
EditorData.NodeContext: Frustrated. Practicing swordplay with little success

Text.Value: Relax - I'm not really a half-orc.
Clear your mind. Past mistakes don't matter. Focus on the present, the target.
You yelp like a frightened dog because of my face?
Oh... yes. When the time comes, it'll be nothing but battle cries from me.
What do you think I'm doing? Brace, parry, swing - UGH!
Interesting technique. Having some trouble?
We need to be ready for a fight - but I'm useless with a sword.

EditorData.NodeContext: 'I'm doing my best, but my best isn't good enough'

Text.Value: Step, parry, step-and-swing! Yes!

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Practicing his swing. Not looking at player. Custom scene viewer needed.

Text.Value: You'd better surrender - that target's a far better fighter.
N-no offence meant. I was just surprised - concentrating on this blasted target.

EditorData.NodeContext: Rowing back on his earlier reaction to a gith player

Text.Value: Calm down - I'm not really githyanki.
Read his thoughts.
Nothing but. Goblins in the wilds, out for blood. And the druids in here, looking to kick us out - or worse.
Har... hrath ajak! And swing! Yes!
Well, I'm in no position to turn down help.
Step-step - hello maggot face, how's your mother? - strike! It worked! Well I'll be.

EditorData.NodeContext: Tries his swordplay - is surprised to succeed

Text.Value: I'll have to keep practising.
And... step, parry, step-step, swing. Yes.

EditorData.NodeContext: Concentrates, then reacts happily upon executing his sword move well.

Text.Value: Demonstrate a swing - show him the fluidity of movement he lacks.
Oh... yes. I'll bite my tongue when the time comes.
Still not landing.
You're not...? For the best, I suppose. I wouldn't have fared well against the real thing.
Leave.
Let's see then. Feint, kick, and - thrust!

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Needs new sneaking practics animation here

Text.Value: You really know what you're doing! Found this by the road - bet you'll put it to good use.
Brace and step, swivel, swing! Yes!
Then you're not angry enough, whelp! Again!
Don't waste good anger on your thoughts - use it on that target!
Leave.
Keep training. When the time comes, you'll drown this place in goblin blood.
One strike means nothing. Keep training, and you may not embarrass yourself in battle.
Keep training. In time, you'll make short work of any goblins.
I'll try and brace them better - like so. Step-brace, parry, swing! Yes!
Try confusing your foe, like when you first saw me. Shout a question at them.
But I'll keep at it. Thank you.
Rage, you say? RrrrrrrrrARGH! Step-brace, parry, swing - ugh.

EditorData.NodeContext: Unconvincing attempt to tap into his rage while swinging his sword.

Text.Value: Leave.
Feint, wait - and thrust!
All right, so like this. Step-step, swivel - UGH!
Try this swing. A little number I call 'The Legend's Strike'.
No wonder you're struggling - you've no balance. Space your feet farther apart.
This isn't a joust. Feint with your sword, then kick between the 'legs' instead.
Like this, then. Focus... focus... and strike! Yes!

Synopsis: Tiefling is practicing his swing on  a dummy, trying to improve. The player can offer advice, potentially improving the tiefling's form.
